                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12991765" author="ryanobjc" created="Tue, 8 Feb 2011 01:43:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;this patch is a little WIP, it&apos;s based on 0.90 with this commit cherry picked in:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/stumbleupon/hbase/commit/67a5b46d069f0e7660d2de998c7b311103708fb4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/stumbleupon/hbase/commit/67a5b46d069f0e7660d2de998c7b311103708fb4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12991790" author="stack" created="Tue, 8 Feb 2011 04:56:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That patch looks fine.  I don&apos;t see a pom edit though included in your patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12991791" author="stack" created="Tue, 8 Feb 2011 04:57:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I meant, the patch looks great.   Its cool getting ICV and parallelGet into our thrift interface.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12993509" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 11 Feb 2011 14:29:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-3117&quot; title=&quot;Update Thrift to 0.5 version&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-3117&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-3117&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also Thrift 0.5 isn&apos;t available in any official repository. The issue is still unresolved (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-363&quot; title=&quot;Maven Deploy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-363&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-363&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12994089" author="larsgeorge" created="Sun, 13 Feb 2011 12:57:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;And now there is 0.6.0 which we should use I presume?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12994152" author="ryanobjc" created="Sun, 13 Feb 2011 20:44:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;thrift 0.5.0 is in the apache maven official repo... there was no&lt;br/&gt;
0.6.0 when i went looking.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12994285" author="lars_francke" created="Mon, 14 Feb 2011 13:19:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ryan, I&apos;m pretty sure Thrift is &lt;b&gt;not&lt;/b&gt; in any repository. As I said the issue is still unresolved and they are looking for help getting it into the repository.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://repository.apache.org/index.html#nexus-search;quick~thrift&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://repository.apache.org/index.html#nexus-search;quick~thrift&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12994567" author="ryanobjc" created="Mon, 14 Feb 2011 23:43:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Try this search:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://repository.apache.org/index.html#nexus-search;quick~libthrift&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://repository.apache.org/index.html#nexus-search;quick~libthrift&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13001598" author="kzk" created="Wed, 2 Mar 2011 20:19:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I prefer 0.6.0 rather than 0.5.0, because &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-923&quot; title=&quot;Event-driven client and server support for C++&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;THRIFT-923&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;THRIFT-923&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; supports asynchronous client in C++.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-923&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-923&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/trunk/CHANGES&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/thrift/blob/trunk/CHANGES&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;FYI&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13001815" author="ryanobjc" created="Thu, 3 Mar 2011 02:07:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;a patch against current trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13001820" author="ryanobjc" created="Thu, 3 Mar 2011 02:14:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Kazuki, 0.6.0 doesnt exist yet (in maven) so we cant depend on it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The on the wire serialization should be the same between 0.5.0 and 0.6.0, so you can use whatever version of C++ client you wish. This is about the &lt;em&gt;hbase serverside&lt;/em&gt; thrift version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13001960" author="kzk" created="Thu, 3 Mar 2011 11:19:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, ryan. Thanks for the comment. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; hbase serverside thrift version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s right. I&apos;ll test the wire compatibility in my environment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Big thanks for your patch anyway!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13002880" author="stack" created="Sat, 5 Mar 2011 00:20:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch (if tests pass).  This breaks old thrift clients?  Needs to go into INCOMPATIBLE CHANGES section.  Add a release note on resolve?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13002881" author="ryanobjc" created="Sat, 5 Mar 2011 00:23:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;it is wire compatible with older clients, tested with an older SU client. There is no actual incompatibility!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13003608" author="hudson" created="Mon, 7 Mar 2011 21:07:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in HBase-TRUNK #1771 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1771/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/HBase-TRUNK/1771/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13005003" author="lars_francke" created="Thu, 10 Mar 2011 09:11:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh, I never saw your answer. Sorry Ryan I never searched for &lt;em&gt;libthrift&lt;/em&gt;, thanks for pointing it out Stack. As this is a custom release by the Hadoop folks are we sure this is not in any way customized by them?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I haven&apos;t looked at the Maven stuff in a while but by being in a custom group we might get a different version by accident as a transitive dependency if any other project decides to do the same as Hadoop.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13005492" author="stack" created="Fri, 11 Mar 2011 05:09:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I didn&apos;t notice the thrift 0.5.0 a hadoop built thing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the warning @LarsF.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017185" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:42:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
